
ID: 3
Title: Checking the trip update according to the new timetable.

Priority:
High

Prerequisites:
None

Test type:
Positive (+)

Environment:
Windows 10, Chrome  80.0.3987.149

Description:
Test describes results for connection between Łódź Kaliska and Wrocław Główny.  Website ‘rozklad-pkp.pl’ should be updated with information included in new train timetable (source: https://polregio.pl/media/14925/linia-nr-200-lodz-kaliska-wroclaw.pdf).

Test scenario:
    1.Go to website: www.rozklad-pkp.pl.
    2.Enter 'From': 'Łódź Kaliska'.
    3.Enter  'To' : 'Wrocław Główny'.
    4.Enter  'Select date': '13 April 2020'.
    5.Click  ‘Select date’ button.
    6.Enter  'Enter the time’ choose  '7:00'.
    7.Click ‘‘Search connection’’.
    8.Click relation which is started at 7:02 (train’s number - R 17501).
    9. Compare it with sources info.

The expected result:
Train ‘R 17501’ is started from Łódź Kaliska to Poznań Główny - there is no intermediate station like Zduńska Wola.

The actual result:
User see route rail from Łódź Kaliska with change in Zduńska Wola. 
